        <div id="container">
            <div id="about" class="detail">
                <div class="wrp">
                    <div class="fs30 c109ce3 fiCielCadena pb10">
                        <h1>"Mizuiku - I love clean water" program </h1>
                    </div>
                    <div class="baiviet">

                        <div class="thongke">

                            <a class='thongke_ngay'>Date posted: 03:26 - 17/06/2017</a>
                            <a class='thongke_luotxem'>Views: 1.414</a>

                            <div class="cochu">
                                <a class="NormalSize" href="javascript:ResetTextSize()">Size</a>
                                <a class="SmallSize" href="javascript:DecreaseTextSize()"></a>
                                <a class="LargeSize" href="javascript:IncreaseTextSize()"></a>
                            </div>
                        </div>

                        <div class="noidung TextSize">
                            <div style="text-align: justify;">
                                &ldquo;Mizuiku&rdquo; is an initiative by Suntory Holdings Limited (Suntory) that was established and implemented in Japan since 2004. The aim of the initiative is to educate and spread awareness on the importance of water conservation and preservation among primary school students. Since then, the program has captivated the participation of over 145,000 primary school children and parents, receiving high praise from the Japanese community and society.</div>
                            <div style="text-align: center;">
                                <img alt="" src="pic/AboutUs/images/IMG_0002.jpg" style="width: 600px; height: 400px;" /></div>
                            <div style="text-align: justify;">
                                In fact, up to 20% of Vietnam&rsquo;s population never had access to clean water. There are many areas that severely lack clean water such as Ben Tre, Bac Ninh and even big cities such as Hanoi and Ho Chi Minh city &ndash; especially in the dry season (statistics by the Institute of Medicine, Labor and Sanitation). Suntory and Suntory PepsiCo Vietnam initiated the Mizuiku &ndash; I love clean water program since 2015 in Vietnam with a goal of spreading sustainable solutions to help protect water resources by providing educational resources to future generations of Vietnam.</div>
                            <div style="text-align: center;">
                                <img alt="" src="pic/AboutUs/images/Cac em hoc sinh duoc hoc ve quy trinh xu ly nuoc thai thong qua cac tro choi(1).jpeg" style="width: 600px; height: 459px;" /></div>
                            <div style="text-align: justify;">
                                The &ldquo;Mizuiku &ndash; I love clean water&rdquo;program aims to educate and raise awareness among primary school students on the importance of water resources in our society, the ways in which we can conserve clean water, what we can contribute to protecting water resources and on our environment as a whole. Through a student-centered approach, the program creative spaces, opportunities for children to practice, stimulate ideas, and help develop their voice when it comes to protecting water resources and the environment.</div>
                            <div style="text-align: center;">
                                <img alt="" src="pic/AboutUs/images/POSTER.jpeg" style="width: 500px; height: 333px;" /></div>
                            <div style="text-align: justify;">
                                From 2015 to 2016, the program commenced in Thanh Oai District and My Duc District in Hanoi, then expanded to Bac Ninh Province and Ho Chi Minh City through the cooperation between Suntory, Suntory PepsiCo Vietnam Beverage company and two partners specializing in environmental education. These partners are Center of Live &amp; Learn for Environment and Community (Live &amp; Learn Center) and Tuong Lai Centre for Health Education and Community Development (Future Center). Over 2 years of implementation, around 14,000 primary school students in 16 elementary schools participated in a series of activities under the &ldquo;Mizuiku &ndash; I love clean water&rdquo; program amounting to impressive results: over 400 Mizuiku lessonsfor more than 5,000 students, 16 Water Festivals for more than 7,700 pupils, 15 SPVB plant tours with 1,300pupils;set-up 10 RO water filtering systems and 6 upgraded restrooms.</div>
                            <div style="text-align: center;">
                                <img alt="" src="pic/AboutUs/images/xu ly nuoc 1.jpeg" style="width: 600px; height: 400px;" /></div>
                            <div style="text-align: justify;">
                                From 2017, the program has entered a new development stage with the strategic partnership between Suntory, Suntory PepsiCo Vietnam Beverage, and Central Council for Ho Chi Minh Young Pioneer Organization, the Vietnam National Student Unionand the strong endorsementof the Ministry of Education &amp; Training, together with educational expert consultancyof the Live &amp; Learn center and the Future center. With a strong partnership foundation, the programexpectsto increase efficacy of the educational component and to expand the program on a national level.</div>
                            <div style="text-align: center;">
                                <img alt="" src="pic/AboutUs/images/Dong song que em MHX.jpg" style="width: 600px; height: 800px;" /></div>
                            <div style="text-align: justify;">
                                The program hopes to contribute to the spiritual and physical development of the students to contribute to preserving water resources for future generations.</div>
                            <div>
                                <br /> PROGRAM ACTIVITIES:
                                <br />
                                <span style="font-size:14px;">- Launching Ceremony<br />
	- Organize training courses (TOT Course) for Head teachers of school-based units of Young Pioneers Organization, Head teachers of grades 3 to 4 at select schools to implement the program, fostering appropriate teaching skills to implement educational activities and extracurricular activities to do with the environment and water conservation under the Mizuiku curriculum.<br />
	- Organize educational training (Mizuiku classes) for students in grade 3 to 4 (at selected schools) under the Mizuiku curriculum covering various appropriate environmental education contents such as water conservation, the water cycle, the role of water in our daily lives, the problems that we are facing with water today, the impact that these problems have on us, the practices of saving water and protecting the environment through water purification experiments and many other practical exercises.<br />
	- Contests to be launched nationwide on the topic of environmental protection and water resource conservation.<br />
	- Water Festivals to be organized at the beneficiary schools which consist of interactive games, knowledge about water, environmental games and rhetoric&rsquo;s on environmental protection.<br />
	- Suntory PepsiCo Vietnam Beverage Plant Tours for students in the third and fourth grade that participate in the program. They are introduced to the factory and its standardized waste treatment processed, production line visits, water purification experiments, creating homemade natural detergents for dish washing etc.<br />
	- Contribute to upgrade clean water facilities at partnered schools, including appropriate support for installation of RO water purification systems, new construction or renovation of toilet for students, painting walls, etc.<br />
	<span style="font-family:calibri,sans-serif;">- Develop program official website and E-learning platform for online studyto increase access to students across the country so that they can enhance their knowledge on water conservation and tune into interesting lectures on the site.</span></span>
                            </div>
                        </div>

